race.comment: PARTY BOSS (9) stalked the pace when resuming at this track and trip last start and never stopped coming to finish a close third. Is sure to have come on from that and is drawn to get another ideal run in transit. Sure to be right there when they quicken. JUDITH'S REVENGE (11) was an eye-catcher here two back and then got the job done over this trip last time when taking closer order under Cahill. Found winning form and there's no reason she can't make it two on the trot. FOURTHTIMELUCKY (3)  progressed nicely last time out to score over 1000m at Wangaratta. Kept fresh with 5 weeks between runs, keeping the legs ticking over with a jump-out. Steps up a level but can keep the ball rolling. CRUCIAL WITNESS (2) has only been sound in her two runs back but is likely improver. Keeping safe.
